TITLE: Signing In with a Fake User - Playwright and Clerk - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates a Playwright test case for signing in with a previously created fake user. Dependencies include the SignIn page object and test utils from Clerk, along with Playwright's test API. Shows how to navigate to the sign-in form and perform user login by supplying email and instant password, and asserts successful authentication. Input parameters are page/context objects and the fake user's credentials.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clerk/javascript/blob/main/integration/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
