TITLE: Using getAuth Helper in Express
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the getAuth helper function to retrieve authentication state and implement custom authorization in an Express application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clerk/javascript/blob/main/packages/express/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { clerkMiddleware, getAuth } from '@clerk/express';
import express from 'express';

const app = express();

// Apply centralized middleware
app.use(clerkMiddleware());

// Protect a route based on authorization status
hasPermission = (request, response, next) => {
  const auth = getAuth(request);

  // Handle if the user is not authorized
  if (!auth.has({ permission: 'org:admin:testpermission' })) {
    return response.status(403).send('Unauthorized');
  }

  return next();
};

app.get('/path', requireAuth, hasPermission, (req, res) => res.json(req.auth));
```

