TITLE: Updating SessionApi.getToken() Usage in Clerk Integrations
DESCRIPTION: Changes to SessionApi.getToken() to return a consistent { data, errors } format. This snippet shows how to use the new format in various Clerk integrations and how to maintain the existing behavior with the new return value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clerk/javascript/blob/main/packages/backend/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-22_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { getAuth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server';

const { getToken } = await getAuth(...);
const jwtString = await getToken(...);

// To keep existing behavior with SessionApi.getToken()
import { ClerkAPIResponseError } from '@clerk/shared/error';

const response = await clerkClient.sessions.getToken(...);

if (response.errors) {
    const { status, statusText, clerkTraceId } = response;
    const error = new ClerkAPIResponseError(statusText || '', {
        data: [],
        status: Number(status || ''),
        clerkTraceId,
    });
    error.errors = response.errors;

    throw error;
}

// the value of the v4 `clerkClient.sessions.getToken(...)`
const jwtString = response.data.jwt;
```

