TITLE: Implementing Clerk Session Management in Next.js Client Component
DESCRIPTION: A Next.js client component that uses the useSession hook from Clerk to manage authentication state. It handles loading states, signed-out states, and displays the time since the session was last active when the user is signed in.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clerk/javascript/blob/main/packages/shared/docs/use-session.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
'use client';

import { useSession } from '@clerk/nextjs';

export default function HomePage() {
  const { isLoaded, session, isSignedIn } = useSession();

  if (!isLoaded) {
    // Handle loading state
    return null;
  }
  if (!isSignedIn) {
    // Handle signed out state
    return null;
  }

  return (
    <div>
      <p>This session has been active since {session.lastActiveAt.toLocaleString()}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

