TITLE: Configuring Current Folder for Clerk Development
DESCRIPTION: Commands for setting up the current working directory with environment variables and dependencies. Creates an environment file, installs dependencies, removes node modules, and links local packages using yalc.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clerk/javascript/blob/main/playground/express/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
touch .env # set PUBLISHABLE_KEY, SECRET_KEY and JWT_KEY from Clerk Dashboard API keys
npm i
rm -rf node_modules/@clerk
yalc add @clerk/express # also add the packages you made changes to, e.g. @clerk/backend @clerk/types.
```

