TITLE: Setting NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS Environment Variable in Shell
DESCRIPTION: This command sets the NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS environment variable to the root CA certificate generated by mkcert. This is necessary because Node.js doesn't use the system root store.
SOURCE: https://github.com/clerk/javascript/blob/main/integration/certs/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
export NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS="$(mkcert -CAROOT)/rootCA.pem"
```

